Subject: [PATCH 353/429] hsu: enable use of dma of hsu_dbg_port
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

There is an issue when to much IRQs are triggered while using the
console (hsu_dbg_port).

With this patch, we switch from PIO mode to DMA mode thus reducing
the number of IRQs on this port.

Signed-off-by: Lo√Øc Akue <loicx.akue@intel.com>
---
 drivers/tty/serial/mfd_core.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/tty/serial/mfd_core.c b/drivers/tty/serial/mfd_core.c
index f7e4ab5d7fd1..11958fbe8700 100644
--- a/drivers/tty/serial/mfd_core.c
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/mfd_core.c
@@ -2302,7 +2302,6 @@ static int serial_port_setup(struct uart_hsu_port *up,
 		serial_hsu_reg.cons = SERIAL_HSU_CONSOLE;
 		if (serial_hsu_reg.cons)
 			serial_hsu_reg.cons->index = index;
-		up->use_dma = 0;
 	} else
 		serial_hsu_reg.cons = NULL;
 	uart_add_one_port(&serial_hsu_reg, &up->port);
